In the Zed keymap file, there appears to be a formatting issue. You have multiple separate objects with the same "context": "Editor", which might cause conflicts. Try combining the Editor bindings into a single object like this:

```json
[
  {
    "context": "Workspace",
    "bindings": {
      // "shift shift": "file_finder::Toggle"
    }
  },
  {
    "context": "Editor",
    "bindings": {
      // "j k": ["workspace::SendKeystrokes", "escape"],
      "cmd right": ["workspace::ActivatePaneInDirection", "Right"],
      "cmd left": ["workspace::ActivatePaneInDirection", "Left"]
    }
  }
]
```

This consolidates all Editor keybindings into a single object, which should resolve any potential conflicts. Also, make sure that:

1. You're using the correct syntax for the key combinations (cmd right and cmd left should be correct)
2. There are no conflicting keybindings in the default keymap
3. You've saved the keymap file and reloaded Zed (if necessary)

If it still doesn't work, you might want to:
1. Check the Zed logs for any error messages
2. Verify that the command names are correct
3. Try using alternative syntax like "cmd+right" instead of "cmd right" (though the space format should work)
